317
00:25:44,160 --> 00:25:48,610
You have never disappointed me once.

318
00:25:48,610 --> 00:25:55,280
Do you really think I've been dictating your life all this time?

319
00:25:55,280 --> 00:26:00,760
That I didn't help while you faced tasks before you?

320
00:26:00,760 --> 00:26:02,950
There was nothing I could do.

321
00:26:02,950 --> 00:26:06,060
You figured everything out yourself.

322
00:26:08,940 --> 00:26:12,340
You always wrote down the answer.

323
00:26:13,640 --> 00:26:15,190
Mom.

324
00:26:15,190 --> 00:26:18,300
Answer it. It's probably my lawyer.

325
00:26:24,330 --> 00:26:26,840
Starting now,

326
00:26:27,540 --> 00:26:30,720
I'm going to sue you.

327
00:26:31,640 --> 00:26:35,100
Since I haven't processed the resignation letter,

328
00:26:35,100 --> 00:26:39,170
you should know you're still on a business trip.

329
00:26:39,170 --> 00:26:44,050
I heard that you used company info to attract investors.

330
00:26:44,050 --> 00:26:45,410
That's nonsense—

331
00:26:45,410 --> 00:26:48,340
Let's determine if it makes sense or not.

332
00:26:48,340 --> 00:26:52,510
You have to stop getting investors due to the lawsuit.

333
00:26:52,510 --> 00:26:54,480
Time is money.

334
00:26:54,480 --> 00:26:56,850
Should we meet in ten days?

335
00:27:01,010 --> 00:27:03,970
Mom, why are you taking it this far—

336
00:27:03,970 --> 00:27:05,830
I told you.

337
00:27:05,830 --> 00:27:08,850
My decision won't change.

338
00:27:09,710 --> 00:27:14,520
What kind of mom would let her son ruin his life?

339
00:27:14,520 --> 00:27:19,590
This won't change my decision, either.

340
00:27:20,370 --> 00:27:22,060
I know.

341
00:27:22,060 --> 00:27:24,620
You take after me.

342
00:27:26,650 --> 00:27:29,580
I'm looking forward to seeing what you'll do.

343
00:27:29,580 --> 00:27:31,960
Clearly, I'm worried.

344
00:27:48,450 --> 00:27:54,190
♫  I know whenever I see you  ♫

345
00:27:54,190 --> 00:28:00,500
♫  My mood is different than usual  ♫

346
00:28:00,500 --> 00:28:07,580
♫  I close my eyes  ♫

347
00:28:07,580 --> 00:28:12,380
♫  I try to forget, but I still get reminded of you  ♫

348
00:28:14,140 --> 00:28:20,020
♫  I miss the time when I didn't know anything  ♫

349
00:28:20,020 --> 00:28:25,280
♫  Looking in your eyes  ♫

350
00:28:26,500 --> 00:28:32,570
♫  I keep circling around and complaining  ♫

351
00:28:32,570 --> 00:28:39,330
♫  But my heart is beating again toward you  ♫

352
00:28:39,330 --> 00:28:47,360
♫  I circle around you like this  ♫

353
00:28:47,360 --> 00:28:50,350
 You were right, Ms. Lee. 

354
00:28:50,350 --> 00:28:54,750
Hu Yeong did the calculation with his smart brain.

355
00:28:54,750 --> 00:28:56,440
He must have made the right decision.

356
00:28:56,440 --> 00:29:02,470
This means I also like you, since he chose you.

357
00:29:03,250 --> 00:29:05,890
So that means—

358
00:29:05,890 --> 00:29:08,530
Come to the U.S. with Hu Yeong.

359
00:29:10,390 --> 00:29:14,370
I don't have the time to get you the plane ticket;

360
00:29:14,370 --> 00:29:16,900
but for now, be ready to move to USA with this.

361
00:29:16,900 --> 00:29:21,100
You won't reach the limit. Don't worry about it.

362
00:29:22,780 --> 00:29:25,920
Wh-What makes you trust me?

363
00:29:25,920 --> 00:29:28,320
You don't know what I would do with this.

364
00:29:28,320 --> 00:29:31,190
I mean, what I would buy with this.

365
00:29:32,240 --> 00:29:35,890
Do you think I trust you?

366
00:29:35,890 --> 00:29:38,700
I trust Hu Yeong's judgment.

367
00:29:41,920 --> 00:29:45,180
I'm going back to the U.S. today.

368
00:29:45,180 --> 00:29:50,430
I'll start a long battle with Hu Yeong.

369
00:29:50,430 --> 00:29:55,700
If you stay by his side, he will feel supported.

370
00:29:56,440 --> 00:30:00,920
I don't think I understand what you're saying at all.

371
00:30:00,920 --> 00:30:06,170
Once he leaves for the U.S., he can't return for a while.

372
00:30:06,170 --> 00:30:08,920
I'm very capable.

373
00:30:10,040 --> 00:30:12,480
So…

374
00:30:12,480 --> 00:30:15,350
let's live in the U.S. together.

375
00:30:18,660 --> 00:30:25,050
He chose to stay with you in Korea and gave up on all the great things.

376
00:30:25,050 --> 00:30:27,190
Can you…

377
00:30:28,720 --> 00:30:31,830
give up this stuff for him?

378
00:30:31,830 --> 00:30:36,920
Or are you not that serious about this relationship?

379
00:30:50,970 --> 00:30:52,890
Lee Hong Ju?

380
00:30:53,940 --> 00:30:55,860
Mr. Kim.

381
00:30:59,700 --> 00:31:02,320
Why are you walking around like that in this cold?

382
00:31:02,320 --> 00:31:07,480
Mr. Kim, you can't walk around with wet hair in this cold.

383
00:31:08,720 --> 00:31:13,080
I'd rather die than hear you worry about me.

384
00:31:15,100 --> 00:31:18,110
Come with me. I'll get you something warm.

385
00:31:18,110 --> 00:31:19,850
Mr. Kim.

386
00:31:21,570 --> 00:31:24,490
Can I treat you today?

387
00:31:28,410 --> 00:31:31,580
No, I said it's okay.

388
00:31:34,330 --> 00:31:38,440
I really wanted to use this today.

389
00:31:39,180 --> 00:31:40,880
I'll make a single payment.

390
00:31:40,880 --> 00:31:43,190
Insert the card there.

391
00:31:48,200 --> 00:31:50,500
The payment went through. 
    

392
00:31:50,500 --> 00:31:53,100
How dare you try to follow him there?

393
00:31:53,100 --> 00:31:55,750
Do you think USA is a neighborhood nearby?

394
00:31:55,750 --> 00:31:58,170
You're right, but…

395
00:31:59,280 --> 00:32:02,300
he likes me a lot.

396
00:32:02,300 --> 00:32:06,510
He says his heart might jump out when I call his name.

397
00:32:06,510 --> 00:32:11,640
I like him, and I want to be with him, too.

398
00:32:11,640 --> 00:32:17,340
It might be nice to get out of here using this chance.

399
00:32:17,340 --> 00:32:21,320
It makes me think I might have a chance.

400
00:32:21,320 --> 00:32:24,590
It's not a terrible proposal, is it?

401
00:32:29,540 --> 00:32:31,520
Then you can just go.

402
00:32:31,520 --> 00:32:34,110
When you get there, you'll figure it out.

403
00:32:34,110 --> 00:32:36,740
People live there just fine, too.

404
00:32:36,740 --> 00:32:39,560
If you don't like it, you can return.

405
00:32:39,560 --> 00:32:43,230
You're right. If I don't like it, I can just come back.

406
00:32:44,320 --> 00:32:48,420
Mr. Kim, I'm really leaving.

407
00:32:55,900 --> 00:33:00,150
Will you really do what I tell you to do?

408
00:33:05,740 --> 00:33:08,810
Geez, you were so disobedient even as a student.

409
00:33:08,810 --> 00:33:12,700
Why would you listen to me now?

410
00:33:12,700 --> 00:33:19,600
Come up with an answer yourself, no matter what it is.

411
00:33:19,600 --> 00:33:23,980
Think carefully about what you really want.

412
00:33:27,970 --> 00:33:30,800
I don't worry about you.

413
00:33:31,650 --> 00:33:37,010
I've seen you come this far, finding good answers.

414
00:33:37,010 --> 00:33:43,980
You've always been my pride as a teacher.

415
00:33:43,980 --> 00:33:48,670
You've been my favorite student in my whole career.

416
00:33:48,670 --> 00:33:51,480
Be proud.

417
00:33:51,480 --> 00:33:53,460
Mr. Kim.

418
00:33:56,190 --> 00:34:00,080
So who is the man you're seeing now?

419
00:34:00,080 --> 00:34:01,910
I wonder if you would remember him.

420
00:34:01,910 --> 00:34:05,420
Kang Hu Yeong, whom I went to school with.

421
00:34:08,820 --> 00:34:11,870
Wh-Who?

422
00:34:11,870 --> 00:34:13,960
K-Kang Hu Yeong?

423
00:34:13,960 --> 00:34:18,270
M-My dear student, the math genius, Kang Hu Yeong?

424
00:34:18,270 --> 00:34:22,680
I think he's a math genius, but I didn't know he was your dear student.

425
00:34:22,680 --> 00:34:26,340
Hey! Why would he date you?

426
00:34:26,340 --> 00:34:29,780
Did you t-tell Hu Yeong about me?

427
00:34:31,130 --> 00:34:33,440
He must have looked for me.

428
00:34:33,440 --> 00:34:39,170
This wouldn't have happened if he talked to me first!

429
00:34:39,170 --> 00:34:40,500
Mr. Kim, how could you?

430
00:34:40,500 --> 00:34:43,350
No, how could you?

431
00:34:57,450 --> 00:34:59,500
Call me when you arrive.

432
00:34:59,500 --> 00:35:01,080
Okay.

433
00:35:01,860 --> 00:35:04,800
I explained everything to Ms. Lee.

434
00:35:04,800 --> 00:35:09,930
I thought you couldn't tell her what you really wanted.

435
00:35:09,930 --> 00:35:13,890
Let's all see each other again in the U.S.

436
00:35:35,910 --> 00:35:37,900
Hong Ju!

437
00:35:37,900 --> 00:35:41,400
Lee Hong Ju!  
 ♫  I hope that you  ♫

438
00:35:41,400 --> 00:35:47,640
♫  Will look at me, too  ♫

439
00:35:49,100 --> 00:36:01,600
♫  You appear in my dreams. I hope I see you in my dream  ♫

440
00:36:02,800 --> 00:36:15,400
♫  I hope you, whom I like, like me, too  ♫

441
00:36:16,500 --> 00:36:29,400
♫  I hope you come a bit closer to my heart now  ♫

