489
00:41:31,840 --> 00:41:33,860
- Is it reserved? 
 - Yes.

490
00:41:33,860 --> 00:41:35,960
It appears you are full.

491
00:41:35,960 --> 00:41:38,120
Oh, Bae Hye Suk.

492
00:41:39,410 --> 00:41:40,900
Were you eating?

493
00:41:40,900 --> 00:41:43,330
Great. I'm hungry, but they don't have a table.

494
00:41:43,330 --> 00:41:45,470
I can join you, right?

495
00:41:47,220 --> 00:41:49,920
Hey, hey, hey.

496
00:41:49,920 --> 00:41:52,080
Finish your food first, then leave.

497
00:41:53,600 --> 00:41:55,200
Hey.

498
00:41:58,820 --> 00:42:01,700
Please eat with me.

499
00:42:01,700 --> 00:42:06,600
Don't leave me behind today, please.

500
00:42:17,530 --> 00:42:19,080
You can only eat.

501
00:42:19,080 --> 00:42:21,790
Of course, I will only eat.

502
00:42:21,790 --> 00:42:25,800
Another bowl of rice, please.

503
00:42:25,800 --> 00:42:30,890
We haven't eaten together in a while. How about a drink?

504
00:42:34,360 --> 00:42:37,870
- Here's the rice you ordered. 
 - Yes.

505
00:42:37,870 --> 00:42:41,320
You two are my regular customers.

506
00:42:41,320 --> 00:42:47,930
I'd like to give you Kwon Sang Pil's signature spicy chicken feet.

507
00:42:47,930 --> 00:42:49,570
Would you like to try them?

508
00:42:49,570 --> 00:42:52,290
We'll take them and a bottle of soju, as well.

509
00:42:52,290 --> 00:42:54,360
Okay, understood.

510
00:42:56,050 --> 00:42:58,200
Their spicy chicken feet are good.

511
00:42:58,200 --> 00:43:00,810
You used to like spicy food.

512
00:43:03,070 --> 00:43:05,550
Here's the soju.

513
00:43:06,860 --> 00:43:10,690
Do... you remember that?

514
00:43:10,690 --> 00:43:13,220
It's been more than 20 years.

515
00:43:13,220 --> 00:43:19,120
It was my first love; I got sick after each date. How could I forget?

516
00:43:22,570 --> 00:43:27,600
Here. Aigoo, it has been a while.

517
00:43:27,600 --> 00:43:32,300
Here you go. Should we do a Love Shot?

518
00:43:39,090 --> 00:43:41,270
Gosh, how nice.

519
00:43:42,180 --> 00:43:45,300
Right, Hye Suk? Do you remember the old days?

520
00:43:45,300 --> 00:43:47,210
- Just eat. 
 - Okay.

521
00:43:47,210 --> 00:43:50,060
Everyone is dating but me.

522
00:44:32,600 --> 00:44:36,900
Did you know this is our first time walking to school together?

523
00:44:39,360 --> 00:44:41,380
You're right.

524
00:44:45,050 --> 00:44:48,800
It would have been nice if we met a little sooner.

525
00:44:48,800 --> 00:44:51,860
It would have been perfect if we met in Grade 10.

526
00:44:51,860 --> 00:44:54,440
Grade 11 would have been fine, too.

527
00:44:56,120 --> 00:44:58,830
The spring of Grade 12 would have been nice.

528
00:45:07,610 --> 00:45:09,890
Let's go to the U.S. together.

529
00:45:14,200 --> 00:45:17,000
I know it won't be an easy decision,

530
00:45:18,510 --> 00:45:21,230
but I can't be without you.

